cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.SY, cs.DC, cs.CY. 

The paper focuses on mitigating Distributed Denial-of-Service attacks in 5G network slicing, which is a networking infrastructure problem. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses security issues, which could place it in the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) category. The proposed mathematical model and simulation/experimental work could also place it in the cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) categories. Finally, the paper's focus on 5G networks and their dedicated resources for different industries could place it in the cs.CY (Computers and Society) category.
